title: Number of oncology practices in the U.S. by region and size 2013
summary: This grouped bar chart represents 4 different Countrys on X-axis for 3 groups 1-2 physicians, 3-6 physicians, and 7 or more physicians. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding Number of new patients.
Out of all 3 groups, 7 or more physicians had the highest Number of new patients in Country South and 1-2 physicians had the lowest Number of new patients in Country West.
In Country West, 3-6 physicians had the maximum Number of new patients and it saw the lowest in Country South out of all 4 Countrys.
Country West and South had the biggest gap of 17.0 between the highest and lowest Number of new patients found for 3-6 physicians.

max_summary: This grouped bar chart represents 4 different Countrys on X-axis for 3 groups 1-2 physicians, 3-6 physicians, and 7 or more physicians. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding Number of new patients.
Out of all 3 groups, 7 or more physicians had the highest Number of new patients in Country South and 1-2 physicians had the lowest Number of new patients in Country West.
In Country West, 3-6 physicians had the highest Number of new patients among all 4 Countrys and it has the lowest Number of new patients in Country South.
The maximum Number of new patients for 3-6 physicians that was found in Country West was 1.59 times larger than the minimum Number of new patients observed in Country South.
Out of all 3 groups, the highest gap between the maximum and minimum Number of new patients was found in case of 1-2 physicians.

In Country South, 7 or more physicians had the highest Number of new patients 75.0 among the 3 groups and in West, 1-2 physicians had the lowest Number of new patients 24.0. The second highest Number of new patients 59.0 was observed for 7 or more physicians in Country South.
Averaging all 3 groups 1-2 physicians, 3-6 physicians, and 7 or more physicians, the Country South is the maximum Number of new patients and Northeast is the minimum Number of new patients.
